  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "Finding \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo can be a bit tricky, as they aren't always prominently displayed. However, here are several strategies you can use:\n\n**1. Kickstarter \"Coming Soon\" Page and Pre-Launch Promotion:**\n\n*   **Kickstarter Pre-Launch Page:** This is the best place to start. Many creators use Kickstarter's built-in pre-launch functionality. Look for a button that says \"Notify me on launch,\" \"Follow this project,\" or similar.\n    *   **How to find it:**\n        *   **Creator's Website/Social Media:** The most common way is for creators to actively promote their \"coming soon\" Kickstarter page on their own websites, social media (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, etc.), newsletters, and online communities. Look for phrases like \"Coming soon to Kickstarter,\" \"Pre-launch Kickstarter,\" or a direct link to their preview page.\n        *   **Kickstarter Search (Less Reliable):** Sometimes, you can find them by searching keywords related to the project in Kickstarter's search bar, but it's not guaranteed. Pre-launch pages don't always rank highly in searches.\n\n**2. Indiegogo \"Coming Soon\" and Pre-Launch Promotion:**\n\n*   **Indiegogo Pre-Launch Page:** Similar to Kickstarter, Indiegogo also offers pre-launch pages. Look for options to \"Follow\" or \"Get notified\" about the upcoming launch.\n    *   **How to find it:**\n        *   **Creator's Website/Social Media:** Just like Kickstarter, creators will promote their pre-launch Indiegogo campaigns on their own channels. Look for links on their website, social media, and email newsletters.\n        *   **Indiegogo Search (Less Reliable):** Use Indiegogo's search bar with relevant keywords, but be aware that pre-launch projects may not be easily found through this method.\n\n**3. Third-Party Websites and Communities:**\n\n*   **Crowdfunding Aggregator Sites:** Several websites track and list crowdfunding projects, including those that are \"coming soon.\"  Some examples include:\n    *   **Gadget Flow:** Often features upcoming tech and design projects.\n    *   **BackerClub:** Sometimes lists pre-launch projects alongside active campaigns.\n    *   **Kicktraq (for Kickstarter):** While primarily used for tracking live campaigns, it sometimes features pre-launch data.\n    *   **Kickstarter and Indiegogo Blog Posts:**  These platforms themselves occasionally highlight upcoming projects in their blog posts or newsletters.\n\n*   **Crowdfunding Communities and Forums:**  Participate in online communities dedicated to crowdfunding, such as:\n    *   **Reddit:**  Subreddits like r/crowdfunding, r/kickstarter, and specific niche subreddits (e.g., r/boardgames for board game projects) often have threads where creators announce their upcoming campaigns.\n    *   **Facebook Groups:** Search for Facebook groups related to crowdfunding or specific product categories.\n    *   **Discord Servers:**  Some creators or communities have Discord servers where they discuss upcoming projects.\n\n*   **Newsletters and Blogs:** Subscribe to newsletters and follow blogs that cover crowdfunding news and upcoming projects.\n\n**4. Following Creators and Companies:**\n\n*   **Follow on Social Media:** If you're interested in a particular creator or company, follow them on social media (Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, etc.) and subscribe to their email newsletter. They will likely announce their upcoming crowdfunding campaigns through these channels.\n\n**Tips for Searching Effectively:**\n\n*   **Use Specific Keywords:** Instead of just searching \"crowdfunding,\" use more specific keywords related to the type of project you're interested in (e.g., \"upcoming RPG Kickstarter,\" \"Indiegogo smart home device pre-launch\").\n*   **Combine Search Terms:**  Use boolean operators (AND, OR, NOT) to refine your searches. For example, \"Kickstarter AND board game AND coming soon.\"\n*   **Check Regularly:**  New projects are being added all the time, so check these resources regularly.\n*   **Set Up Alerts:**  Use Google Alerts or similar services to get notified when new content matching your search terms is published online.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **\"Coming Soon\" Doesn't Guarantee Success:**  Just because a project has a pre-launch page doesn't mean it will launch successfully or even launch at all.\n*   **Do Your Research:**  Always do thorough research on the creator and the project before backing any crowdfunding campaign, even those that are \"coming soon.\" Read the project description carefully, check the creator's track record, and be aware of the risks involved.\n*   **No Guarantee of Launch Date:**  Launch dates are often tentative and subject to change.\n\nBy using these strategies, you'll significantly increase your chances of discovering exciting new crowdfunding projects before they officially launch on Kickstarter and Indiegogo. Good luck!\n",
